# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# tokenized-real-estate — environment configuration
#
# STEP 0 — Generate a dedicated testnet wallet (one-time setup):
#
#     npm run generate:wallet
#
#   This prints a fresh address + private key. Paste the private key below.
#   The address shown needs to be funded with Sepolia ETH before deploying.
#
#   WHY a dedicated wallet?
#   • The private key must be stored in this plain-text file — using a key
#     that also holds real ETH or mainnet tokens would be a serious security
#     risk if the file is ever leaked or accidentally committed.
#   • A testnet-only key has zero real-world value, so a leak is just an
#     inconvenience. This is the standard professional practice.
#   • MetaMask "accounts" share a seed phrase — any one of them could drain
#     your mainnet funds if exported. Generate a standalone key here instead.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values:
#     cp .env.example .env        (macOS / Linux)
#     copy .env.example .env      (Windows)
#
# NEVER commit your real `.env`. It is already in .gitignore.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Network ---------------------------------------------------------------
# JSON-RPC endpoint for the Sepolia testnet.
# Get a free URL from one of these providers (all have a free tier):
#   Alchemy  : https://alchemy.com          → Create App → Ethereum Sepolia
#   Infura   : https://infura.io            → Create Project → Sepolia endpoint
#   QuickNode: https://quicknode.com        → Create Endpoint → Ethereum Sepolia
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL="https://eth-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_API_KEY"

# --- Deployer / Issuer key -------------------------------------------------
# Private key of the DEDICATED TESTNET wallet generated by `npm run generate:wallet`.
# This account:
#   - deploys all contracts (needs gas → fund it first),
#   - owns the token, identity registry, factories, and claim issuer,
#   - acts as the token agent (mint) and identity-registry agent (KYC),
#   - custodies the initial token supply.
#
# Fund the matching address on Sepolia before running the deploy scripts.
# Faucets (see `npm run generate:wallet` output for direct links):
#   Google (no signup): https://cloud.google.com/application/web3/faucet/ethereum/sepolia
#   Alchemy:            https://sepoliafaucet.com
#   Infura:             https://www.infura.io/faucet/sepolia
#   PoW (no signup):    https://sepolia-faucet.pk910.de
DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY="0xyour_deployer_private_key_here"

# --- Claim signer key (OPTIONAL) -------------------------------------------
# Private key of the account that cryptographically signs KYC claims on behalf
# of the Claim Issuer. In production this would be a separate, hardware-secured
# key. Leave blank to use the deployer key (fine for a PoC).
# This account NEVER needs ETH — it only signs messages off-chain.
CLAIM_SIGNER_PRIVATE_KEY=""

# --- Investor address (OPTIONAL) -------------------------------------------
# Address of the investor wallet that script 03 onboards (KYC + register).
# This is only ever a token RECIPIENT, so its private key is NEVER required.
# If left blank, script 03 generates a random investor address automatically.
INVESTOR_ADDRESS=""
